## Relay-A6 人类友好的接力运行标题架构
**Status:** implemented
**Module:** relay
**Tags:** stack:both, module:relay
**Depends on:** Relay-G14, Relay-G13

**状态：** 已批准

## 概述

接力运行目前显示原始 UUID（例如 `run-6ddc1312`），对用户来说毫无意义。本架构添加从任务描述派生的人类可读标题，并允许用户在 Relay 视图中直接编辑标题，使接力运行在接力视图、聊天卡片和运行历史中一目了然。

### 问题

`RunEntry` 结构体存储 `run_id`（UUID）但没有显示标题。每个引用接力运行的 UI 界面要么显示原始 UUID（不可读），要么显示完整任务描述（太长）。两者都不是良好的用户体验。

### 解决方案

在运行创建时根据任务描述自动生成标题。将其与 `run_id` 一起存储。将标题作为主要信息显示，`run_id` 作为次要信息。

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Run Creation"
        SR[spawn_relay tool] -->|task string| TT[title_from_task]
        TT -->|max 40 chars| RE[RunEntry.title]
        RE -->|persist| RS[RunStore]
    end
    subgraph "API Response"
        RS -->|RunSummary| API[/api/forge/relay/runs]
        RS -->|RunState| API2[/api/forge/relay/runs/:id]
    end
    subgraph "UI Surfaces"
        API -->|title + run_id subtitle| RV[RelayView run list]
        API -->|title + run_id subtitle| CC[Chat relay card]
        API -->|title + run_id subtitle| RH[Run history]
    end
```

### 标题生成算法

```
function title_from_task(task: string) -> string:
    // 1. 去除开头的 "## Task\n" 或 markdown 标题（如果存在）
    cleaned = task.trim()
    if cleaned starts with "## ":
        cleaned = first line after "## "
    if cleaned starts with "# ":
        cleaned = first line after "# "

    // 2. 取第一句或前 N 个词
    first_sentence = split on '. ' or '\n' and take first part
    words = first_sentence.split(' ')

    // 3. 截断至最多 40 个字符，在单词边界处断开
    if words.join(' ').length > 40:
        result = ""
        for word in words:
            if (result + " " + word).length > 40: break
            result += (result ? " " : "") + word
        return result + "..."
    
    return words.join(' ')
```

### 数据模型变更

```rust
// RunEntry — 添加 title 字段
pub struct RunEntry {
    pub run_id: String,        // 已有: "run-6ddc1312"
    pub title: String,         // 新增: "Add OAuth2 login support"
    pub flow_id: String,       // 已有
    pub status: RunStatus,     // 已有
    // ... 其余不变
}
```

前端类型：

```typescript
interface RunSummary {
  run_id: string      // "run-6ddc1312"
  title: string       // "Add OAuth2 login support"  ← 新增
  flow_id: string
  status: string
  // ... 其余不变
}
```

### API 变更

| 端点 | 变更 |
|----------|--------|
| `POST /api/forge/relay/runs`（spawn） | 从 `task` 字段接受/派生 `title` |
| `GET /api/forge/relay/runs` | 在每个 `RunSummary` 中返回 `title` |
| `GET /api/forge/relay/runs/:id` | 在 `RunState` 中返回 `title` |
| `PATCH /api/forge/relay/runs/:id/title` | 更新运行的自定义标题；空字符串清除自定义标题并回退到自动生成标题 |

### 关键架构决策

| 决策 | 选择 | 理由 |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| 标题生成时机 | 启动时（非惰性） | 一致，展示时无需计算 |
| 标题来源 | 任务描述的第一句话 | 最具描述性，由用户撰写 |
| 最大长度 | 40 个字符 | 适合侧边栏/卡片，无需截断 |
| 回退策略 | 若 title 为空则显示 `run_id` | 始终展示有意义的内容 |
| 可编辑性 | 可编辑（点击标题进入编辑模式） | 用户可以根据需要重命名，空标题回退到自动生成 |
| 存储方式 | `RunMetadata.title` 字段 | 简单，与 `initial_task` 一起存储；清除时回退到自动生成 |

### 标题编辑流程

```
User clicks title in RelayView
  → input enters edit mode with current title
  → User types new title
  → Enter: PATCH /api/forge/relay/runs/:id/title { title }
  → Esc or empty submit: cancel / revert to auto-generated title
  → Backend updates RunMetadata.title and persists
  → Backend broadcasts run_title_updated SSE event
  → Frontend updates currentRun and runs list
```

### 触发条件

- 标题在 `spawn_relay` 工具创建新的 `RunEntry` 时自动生成。
- 用户在 Relay 视图中点击标题进入编辑模式。

### 数据流

```
[用户聊天 → Advisor → spawn_relay(task: "Add OAuth2 login support")]
    → title_from_task("Add OAuth2 login support") → "Add OAuth2 login support"
    → RunEntry { run_id: "run-6ddc1312", title: "Add OAuth2 login support", ... }
    → 持久化到 RunStore
    → 在后续所有 API 响应中返回
```

### 设计亮点

通过在启动时根据任务描述生成标题，我们避免了额外的 API 调用或惰性计算。标题质量取决于任务描述的第一句话——而这由 Advisor 撰写。由于 Advisor 已经撰写了描述性的任务摘要，因此标题将是有意义的。

| 方案 | 优点 | 缺点 |
|---|---|---|
| **启动时从任务自动生成**（已选） | 零用户操作、一致、始终可用 | 依赖于良好的任务描述 |
| 用户输入标题 | 标题完美 | 额外步骤，用户可能跳过 |
| LLM 生成标题 | 可能比任务摘录更好 | 额外 Token 成本、延迟 |
| 任务前 N 个字符 | 最简单 | 可能在单词中间截断，不美观 |

### 修改的文件

| 文件 | 变更 |
|------|--------|
| `backend/src/relay/title.rs` | 标题生成算法 `generate_title()` |
| `backend/src/relay/store.rs` | 添加 `update_run_metadata()`；`RunMetadata` 存储 `title` 和 `initial_task` |
| `backend/src/relay/api.rs` | 添加 `UpdateRunTitleRequest` DTO、`update_run_title_handler()` 和 `PATCH /runs/:id/title` 路由 |
| `frontend/src/composables/useRelay.ts` | 添加 `updateRunTitle()`；监听 `run_title_updated` SSE 事件 |
| `frontend/src/views/RelayView.vue` | 标题支持点击编辑、Enter 保存、Esc 取消 |
| `frontend/src/i18n/locales/en.json` / `zh.json` | 添加 `relay.editTitle` 文案 |

## Relay-A7 Relay Report PDF Export Architecture (Consolidated)
**Status:** approved
**Module:** relay
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:relay
**Depends on:** Relay-G15

### 概述

用户需要将接力运行报告导出为 PDF 文档，以便分享、归档和离线评审。PDF 应包含运行元数据、执行时间线、规范变更和交付物摘要。使用客户端 `jspdf` + `jspdf-autotable` 生成，无需后端 PDF 库。

### 问题

接力运行数据被困在浏览器中。目前无法：
- 与没有 AutoForge 访问权限的利益相关者分享接力报告
- 为合规或复盘归档接力执行历史
- 生成自主流水线所做工作的可打印摘要

### 解决方案

前端 PDF 导出。数据已存在于前端 RunState 中。`PdfGenerator.ts` 工具类将 RunState 转换为格式化的 PDF 文档。

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Frontend — PDF Generation"
        EB[Export Button] --> PG[PdfGenerator.ts]
        PG --> JPDF[jspdf + autotable]
        PG --> DATA[RunState API data]
        DATA --> META[Run metadata]
        DATA --> HIST[Execution history]
        DATA --> SPECS[Spec changes]
        DATA --> DELIV[Deliverables]
    end

    subgraph "PDF Document"
        P1[Cover: title, flow, status, dates]
        P2[Summary: metrics table]
        P3[Timeline: step-by-step]
        P4[Specs: sections modified]
        P5[Deliverables: files list]
    end

    JPDF --> P1
    JPDF --> P2
    JPDF --> P3
    JPDF --> P4
    JPDF --> P5
```

### 触发条件

用户点击接力视图头部或运行详情卡片中的"导出 PDF"按钮。按钮仅在选中已完成的运行时才可用。

### 数据流

```
[用户点击导出 PDF]
    → mapRunState() 将前端 RunState 转换为扁平的 PdfData 接口
    → PdfGenerator.generate(pdfData) 在内存中构建页面
    → PdfGenerator.save(pdfData) 触发浏览器下载
    → 浏览器下载 PDF
    → 无服务器参与
```

### 设计亮点

客户端 PDF 生成是交付价值的最简单架构。PDF 所需的每一块接力数据都已加载在前端——我们只需将其序列化为格式化文档。无需后端变更。

### 关键架构决策

| 决策 | 选择 | 理由 |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| 生成位置 | 客户端（浏览器） | 无服务端依赖、即时、支持离线 |
| PDF 库 | jspdf + jspdf-autotable | 轻量（gzip 后约 200KB）、无原生依赖、内置表格支持 |
| 数据源 | 现有 RunState API | 无需新的后端端点 |
| 触发方式 | 用户点击按钮 | 不自动生成；用户控制时机 |
| 文件命名 | `relay-{title-slug}-{date}.pdf` | 可识别、按日期排序 |

### 权衡

| 方案 | 优点 | 缺点 |
|----------|------|------|
| **客户端 jspdf**（已选） | 零后端依赖、即时、支持离线 | 样式有限，自定义字体不易 |
| 服务端（wkhtmltopdf/WeasyPrint） | 丰富的 HTML→PDF、完整 CSS 支持 | 后端依赖、延迟、资源消耗 |
| 打印到 PDF（window.print()） | 零代码 | 布局不可预测，用户必须知道 Ctrl+P |
| Puppeteer headless | 渲染完美 | 需要 Node.js 服务端，资源消耗大 |

### 使用的 API 数据

| 端点 | 使用的字段 |
|----------|------------|
| `GET /api/forge/relay/runs/:id` | `run_id`, `title`, `flow_id`, `status`, `mode`, `created_at`, `completed_at`, `tokens_used`, `steps` |
| `GET /api/forge/relay/runs/:id/history` | `handoffs[]` 含 `from`, `to`, `timestamp`, `summary`, `tokens_used` |

无需新的后端端点。

### PDF 文档结构

| 页码 | 内容 | 布局 |
|------|---------|--------|
| 1 — 封面 | 标题、运行元数据表 | 居中标题、元数据 autoTable |
| 2 — 摘要 | 指标概览 + 每步 Token 表 | 两个 autoTable |
| 3 — 时间线 | 按时间顺序的步骤执行 | 带时间戳的 autoTable |
| 4 — 规范变更 | 修改的章节、动作、条目 ID | autoTable（可选，仅有变更时显示）|
| 5 — 交付物 | 生成的文件/规范/报告 | autoTable（可选，仅有交付物时显示）|

## Relay-A8 Cost Breakdown 历史运行 Per-Profession Token 统计架构
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:backend

## Overview
Fix the Cost Breakdown pie chart to correctly display per-profession token consumption when viewing historical relay runs.

## Problem Statement
During live relay execution, the frontend accumulates `professionTokens` from SSE events (per-step token usage) and renders a pie chart. When loading a historical run via `loadRun`, this data is **not** reconstructed from the persisted run state — the pie chart shows empty/zero.

## Root Cause
1. The backend `RunEntry` / `StepState` stores cumulative token counts per step but does **not** aggregate a per-profession token breakdown into the API response.
2. The frontend `loadRun` function fetches run data but does not populate the reactive `professionTokens` map from the step history.

## Solution — Two Changes

### Change 1: Backend — Compute `profession_tokens` in API Response
In the `get_run` handler (or the serialization of `RunEntry`), aggregate `profession_tokens: HashMap<String, u64>` by iterating over each `StepState` in the run and summing `step.tokens_used` grouped by `step.profession`.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as Frontend (loadRun)
    participant API as GET /api/relay/runs/:id
    participant Store as RunStore
    participant DB as run JSON file

    FE->>API: GET /api/relay/runs/:id
    API->>Store: get_run(run_id)
    Store->>DB: read run JSON
    DB-->>Store: RunEntry
    Store-->>API: RunEntry
    API->>API: compute profession_tokens from steps
    Note over API: for step in run.steps:<br/>map[step.profession] += step.tokens_used
    API-->>FE: JSON { ..., profession_tokens: { "architect": 12000, "coder": 8500 } }
```


### Change 2: Frontend — Populate `professionTokens` in `loadRun`
After fetching the run, extract `profession_tokens` from the response and write it into the reactive `professionTokens` ref that the pie chart consumes.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User clicks run
    participant RV as RelayView
    participant API as fetch GET /runs/:id
    participant Chart as CostBreakdownChart

    User->>RV: selectRun(run_id)
    RV->>API: loadRun(run_id)
    API-->>RV: { run, steps, profession_tokens }
    RV->>RV: currentRun = run
    RV->>RV: professionTokens.clear()
    RV->>RV: professionTokens[k] = v for each entry
    Note over RV: professionTokens now populated
    Chart->>RV: watch(professionTokens)
    Chart->>Chart: re-render pie slices
```


## Data Model

### Backend: `RunDetailResponse` (augmented)
```rust
pub struct RunDetailResponse {
    // ... existing fields from RunEntry ...
    pub steps: Vec<StepState>,
    pub profession_tokens: HashMap<String, u64>,  // NEW: profession → total tokens
}
```

### Frontend: Type update
```typescript
interface RunDetail {
  // ... existing fields ...
  profession_tokens: Record<string, number>  // NEW
}
```

## Edge Cases
| Case | Handling |
|---|---|
| Run has no steps yet | `profession_tokens` = `{}` (empty map) — chart shows "No data" |
| Step has `tokens_used = 0` | Still included in aggregation; profession entry may have 0 total |
| Step `profession` is `None`/empty | Skip or group under `"unknown"` key |
| Live run SSE events arrive | `professionTokens` continues to accumulate; `loadRun` overwrites with authoritative totals |

## Trade-offs
| Alternative | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| **Read-time aggregation (chosen)** | No schema migration, always accurate, simple | O(steps) compute per GET |
| Persist `profession_tokens` in RunEntry on disk | O(1) read | Must update on every step completion, risk of drift |
| Compute in frontend from steps array | Backend unchanged | Frontend must know aggregation logic, data already available |

## Files Involved
- `backend/src/relay/store.rs` — `RunEntry`, `StepState`, `get_run`
- `backend/src/relay/api.rs` — `get_run` handler, add `profession_tokens`
- `frontend/src/views/RelayView.vue` — `loadRun` function, `professionTokens` ref

## Relay-A9 Segmented Token Progress Bar Architecture
**Status:** approved

## Overview

Replace the inline Cost Breakdown pie chart panel in RelayView.vue with a multi-color segmented progress bar embedded in the budget bar area. Each profession's token usage is shown as a colored segment proportional to its consumption. A hover tooltip displays a horizontal bar chart comparing all agents' token usage and percentages.

## Problem Statement

The current Cost Breakdown panel (RelayView.vue lines 326-370) is an inline SVG pie chart + legend card occupying a full `.cost-panel` section. This creates two problems:
1. **Visual fragmentation** — Token cost information is decoupled from the budget bar (lines 99-111), forcing users to look in two places.
2. **Space waste** — A full card for a pie chart is excessive when the data can be communicated more compactly.

The budget bar already shows total token consumption as a single-color progress bar. Merging per-profession breakdown into it eliminates the separate panel entirely.

## Architecture

### Component Structure

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "RelayView.vue"
        BB["Budget Bar Area<br/>(lines 99-111)"]
        SPB["SegmentedProgressBar<br/>(NEW component)"]
        TT["AgentBreakdownTooltip<br/>(inline in SPB)"]
    end
    
    subgraph "REMOVED from RelayView.vue"
        CBP[".cost-panel div ❌<br/>(lines 326-370)"]
        PIE["Inline SVG Pie Chart ❌"]
        LEG[".pie-legend ❌"]
        PCC["pieSlices computed ❌"]
        PCL["professionColors map ❌"]
    end

    BB --> SPB
    SPB -.->|hover| TT
    
    CBP -.->|deleted| X["✗"]
    PIE -.->|deleted| X
    LEG -.->|deleted| X
    PCC -.->|deleted| X
    PCL -.->|deleted| X
    
    style CBP fill:#fdd,stroke:#c00
    style PIE fill:#fdd,stroke:#c00
    style LEG fill:#fdd,stroke:#c00
    style PCC fill:#fdd,stroke:#c00
    style PCL fill:#fdd,stroke:#c00
    style SPB fill:#dfd,stroke:#0a0
    style TT fill:#dfd,stroke:#0a0
```

### Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant SSE as SSE Events / loadRun
    participant uR as useRelay.ts
    participant PT as _professionTokens (singleton ref)
    participant UPS as useProfessionSegments
    participant RV as RelayView.vue
    participant SPB as SegmentedProgressBar
    participant TT as AgentBreakdownTooltip

    SSE->>uR: token_delta { profession, tokens_used }
    uR->>PT: _professionTokens[profession] += tokens_used
    uR-->>RV: professionTokens ref exposed
    RV->>UPS: useProfessionSegments(professionTokens)
    UPS-->>RV: { segments, totalUsed, tooltipEntries }
    RV-->>SPB: :segments :total-budget :total-used props
    SPB->>SPB: render colored segments proportional to budget

    User->>SPB: mouseenter
    SPB->>TT: show tooltip (80ms delay)
    TT->>TT: render horizontal bar chart sorted desc
    TT-->>User: "architect: 12.4k (35.2%)<br/>coder: 8.5k (24.1%)<br/>..."

    User->>SPB: mouseleave
    SPB->>TT: hide tooltip (150ms debounce)
```

### Trigger Conditions
- **Segment update**: Every time `_professionTokens` reactive ref changes (SSE `step_delta` event or `loadRun()` with `data.profession_tokens`)
- **Tooltip show**: `mouseenter` on the segmented bar (80ms delay)
- **Tooltip hide**: `mouseleave` on the segmented bar (150ms debounce)
- **Budget warning**: Total tokens cross 70% or 90% of `currentRun.budget_limit`

### Data Model

#### ProfessionSegment (composable output → component prop)
```typescript
interface ProfessionSegment {
  profession: string           // e.g. "architect", "coder", "tester"
  tokens: number               // total tokens consumed by this profession
  color: string                // CSS color value from PROFESSION_PALETTE
}
```

#### TooltipBarEntry (composable output → tooltip prop)
```typescript
interface TooltipBarEntry {
  profession: string
  tokens: number
  percentage: number           // tokens / totalUsed * 100, 1 decimal
  color: string
}
```

#### SegmentedProgressBar Props
```typescript
interface SegmentedProgressBarProps {
  segments: ProfessionSegment[]
  totalBudget: number          // currentRun.budget_limit
  totalUsed: number            // computed from segments
  warnThreshold?: number       // default 0.7
  dangerThreshold?: number     // default 0.9
}
```

#### Profession Color Palette
```typescript
const PROFESSION_PALETTE: Record<string, string> = {
  advisor:    '#6366f1',  // indigo
  architect:  '#8b5cf6',  // violet
  planner:    '#3b82f6',  // blue
  coder:      '#10b981',  // emerald
  tester:     '#f59e0b',  // amber
  reviewer:   '#ef4444',  // red
  documenter: '#06b6d4',  // cyan
  gofer:      '#64748b',  // slate
  _default:   '#94a3b8',  // gray
}
```

### Budget Warning Overlay

Budget warning thresholds (70% / 90%) are communicated via the bar's **border glow**, not by changing segment colors:
- **< 70%**: Default (no glow)
- **70–90%**: Amber border glow (`box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.3)`)
- **> 90%**: Red border glow (`box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.4)`)

Segments remain colored by profession — budget warning is a separate visual layer.

### Tooltip: Horizontal Bar Chart

Floating popover (`position: absolute`, no library dependency) above the bar on hover:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│  Token Breakdown                │
│  ─────────────────────────────  │
│  architect  ████████████  35.2% │
│  coder      ██████████    24.1% │
│  tester     ████████      19.8% │
│  planner    █████         12.4% │
│  reviewer   ███            5.1% │
│  documenter ██             3.4% │
│  ─────────────────────────────  │
│  Total: 35.2k / 100.0k         │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
```

Each row: `[color dot] [profession name] [proportional bar] [percentage]`
Sorted by tokens descending. Mini-bars are pure CSS (`width: %`).

## Edge Cases

| Case | Handling |
|---|---|
| No tokens consumed yet | Show empty bar with placeholder text centered |
| Single profession | One segment fills the whole bar; tooltip shows one row at 100% |
| `professionTokens` is empty `{}` | Same as no tokens — empty state |
| Very small profession (< 2% of total) | Segment rendered with min 2px width; tooltip still lists it |
| Budget is 0 or undefined | Bar renders segments proportionally without budget marker; no warning thresholds |
| Tooltip near viewport edge | Popover flips below the bar if no space above |

## Trade-offs

| Alternative | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| **Inline segmented bar + hover tooltip (chosen)** | Compact, no extra panel, discoverable on hover | Requires hover interaction for details |
| Keep pie chart but make it smaller | Familiar visual | Still wastes space, doesn't consolidate |
| Always-visible stacked legend below bar | Details always visible | Clutters the compact budget area |
| Click to expand (collapsible panel) | Progressive disclosure | Extra click; hover is faster for quick glance |

## Design Highlight

Merging the cost breakdown into the budget bar follows the "progressive disclosure" pattern — the bar gives an instant visual overview, and the hover tooltip provides the detailed breakdown. This eliminates an entire UI panel while preserving all information.

## Verified Code References

- **Budget bar area**: `frontend/src/views/RelayView.vue:99-111` — the `.budget-bar-container` div with mono-color `.budget-fill`
- **Cost Breakdown panel**: `frontend/src/views/RelayView.vue:326-370` — inline SVG pie chart + `.pie-legend`
- **professionTokens ref**: `frontend/src/composables/useRelay.ts:16` — `_professionTokens` singleton ref
- **professionTokens population**: `frontend/src/composables/useRelay.ts:~261` — `loadRun()` sets `_professionTokens.value = data.profession_tokens`
- **budgetUsedPercent**: `frontend/src/composables/useRelay.ts:104` — existing computed
- **No separate CostBreakdownChart.vue file exists** — the pie chart is inline in RelayView.vue

